an\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25651,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/20\/wudu-wipe-socks-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":22931,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping socks three days in travel, one day residency","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 20, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali ibn Abi Talib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, permitted wiping over leather socks for three day and nights for the traveler, and one day and night for the resident. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 276 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Nawawi said, \u201cOur scholars\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19921,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/10\/08\/umar-ask-sheep-euphrates\/","url_meta":{"origin":22931,"position":5},"title":"Umar on Rights: I fear Allah will ask me about my animals","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 8, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Dawud ibn Ali reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIf a lost sheep under my care were to die on the banks of the Euphrates, I would expect Allah the Exalted to question me about it on the Day of Resurrection.\u201d Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304' 137\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuam